    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's risky but my doctor is always so dismissive about anything that isn't a prescription pill. i just want to feel more in control of my own health. if i was really careful and just upped the dose of the garlic and kept the smoothies consistent so my levels stay even, wouldn't that basically be doing the same thing as the warfarin? it just seems like such an extreme way to manage it with just a pill.",
